    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing initialization of rach_present field in UL TTI requests\n\n### Summary\nThe `rach_present` field in `nfapi_nr_ul_tti_request_t` structures was not being properly initialized to 0 in two key locations. This field is conditionally mandatory per 3GPP specifications and should be set to 0 when no RACH is present in the slot.\n\nThis issue could lead to undefined behavior when the scheduler processes UL TTI requests with uninitialized `rach_present` values, potentially causing incorrect RACH detection or scheduling conflicts.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/gNB_scheduler.c`: Added `future_ul_tti_req->rach_present = 0;` in the `clear_nr_nfapi_information` function to ensure proper initialization when clearing UL TTI requests.\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/gNB_scheduler_primitives.c`: Added `req->rach_present = 0;` in the `UL_tti_req_ahead_initialization` function to ensure proper initialization during buffer setup.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Run the gNB with NR configuration\n2. Monitor UL TTI request processing\n3. Observe that `rach_present` field may contain garbage values when not explicitly set\n4. This can cause incorrect scheduling decisions when the uninitialized value is interpreted as RACH being present\n\nThe fix ensures that `rach_present` is always properly initialized to 0 as required by 3GPP specifications when no RACH is scheduled, preventing potential scheduling issues.\n"
}